JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates soccer player Patrick Phungwayo appeared at the Palm Ridge Magistrate s Court on Tuesday facing a charge of attempted murder, assault and possession of an unlicensed firearm.Phungwayo, 29, and his brother Phelelani Aubrey Phungwayo, were at a party in Spruitview, east of Johannesburg, during the May Day weekend when they were involved in an altercation with another man.The man was allegedly assaulted and shot at. The bullet hit his ring finger.The Pirates left-back and his brother were arrested on Monday, but police failed to find the firearm that was allegedly used in the incident.READ: Meyiwa Killing: charges dropped due to lack of evidenceOn Tuesday, Magistrate Van Der Hoevel granted the brothers bail of R2,000 each.The matter was postponed to 23 June for further investigations.African News Agency